BRIEF HISTORY OF THE PUBLIC LIBRARIES COMMISSION' A SURVEY OF 25 YEARS.A REVISED VERSION OF A PAPER GIVEN TO THE MUSIC LIBRARY ASSOCIATION IN BOSTON,3 MAR 78, AND, IN A DIFFERENT FORM TO THE PUBLIC LIBRARIES COMMISSION DURINGTHE SALZBURG MEETING OF IAML, 2 JULY 78. SUMMARISES THE DEVELOPMENT ANDACHIEVEMENTS OF THE PUBLIC LIBRARIES COMMISSION, WHICH WAS ESTABLISHED IN 1954AS PART OF IAML. DISCUSSES BRIEFLY THE WORK OF THE COMMISSION IN PROMOTING ANDSUPPORTING THE DEVELOPMENT OF PUBLIC MUSIC LIBRARIES, AND NOTES THECONTRIBUTION MADE BY ITS 1ST PRESIDENT, DR ALFONS OTT